Theoretical overwiev of phonetic articulation disorders, myofunctional disorders and CLP speech is given. The development of compensatory articulation disorders related with clefting is explained. The student will be able to assess the articulation, knows objective and subjective assessment methods of velopharyngeal function. An overview of speech therapy methods  is given.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give a theoretical overview of phonetic speech disorders and cleft palate speech disorders: overwiev of manifestation, mechanisms,  assessment and treatment .Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student can assess symptoms of phonetic speech disorders and of speech impairment associated with clefting.
The student can explain different mechanisms of CLP speech and phonetic speech disorders.
The student knows assessment methods of velopharyngeal function and articulation.
The student can choose the intervention/treatment methods and specific materials to be used in therapy sessions.
The student is able to plan a therapy session with cleft palate impaired child .
